<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Wyndal:
[B]I have a 16 HIE Cleric that I play once a week with 5 friends.  Our group consists of cleric (me), enchanter, warrior, ranger, and bard.  Sometimes, we pickup a sixth player.  We play these characters only once a week because of one friend's RL commitments.  The rest of us play other characters during the week.  This is my first cleric and I must say that I enjoy playing him more than my bard or druid.  I'm having some problems with heals and I need some sage advise.

My spell lineup during combat consists of yaulp, root, stun, smite, expulse undead, light heal, heal, divine aura.  I use one of the slots to swapout buff spell.  My normal technique is to watch the battle and heal as necessary.  I stun/root stray mobs on the enchanter and keep a very watchful eye on the bard's health bar.  When fighting just one mob, I melee some and nuke a little just to do something different.  But meleeing and nuking is an exception and not the way I normally play.

My problem is that our bard and enchanter are dying too much (in my opinion), and this is happening when I have plenty of mana.  During the start of the fight, I have been healing the bard when he drops 1 to 1.5 bubbles.  He drops so fast and my heal spell cycles so slow (to me) that I try to keep him from dropping below 50 percent.  Typically on a multi-mob pull, things go good until the enchanter gets resisted.  Then I start getting attacked and althought I have AC and HP to absorb the blows, I can't get a heal off.  In the time it takes me to stun/root park the mob, then fire a heal at the bard or enchanter, one or both are dead.  I feel real bad when one of them dies; I actually take it personal.  Here I am with most of my health, most of my mana, and I have 1 or 2 dead friends on the ground.

My enchanter friend and I were talking this morning about when to heal.  We agreed that the early healing on my part probably moved me to the top of the agrro list.  Example: 3 mobs; group fights 1 mob; enchanter mezzes 2 mobs; cleric heals bard for couple 100 HPs; mezz breaks and enchanter gets resisted on first try; both mobs pay visit to cleric.  Now bard is below 50 percent and dropping fast.  Cleric's heal spell keeps getting interrupted because he's getting beat on and someone dies.

I hope my post is not too confusing to read; I really need some help on technique.  I want to be a good cleric.  Please help me!!

Wyndal
16 High-Elf Cleric
Veeshan

P.S.  We are currently fighting in Unrest.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
